<topic id="attribute_overview">
    <title>Attributes</title>
    <shortdesc>The part of the data model describing the characteristics of Classes. Attributes
        define the data within the data model.</shortdesc>
    <body>
        <p>Within this publication, the names of Attributes are styled like this: <ph
                outputclass="attribute">NHS NUMBER</ph>.</p>
        <p>Classes, Attributes and the Relationships between Classes collectively define the NHS
            Data Model. </p>
        <p>A Class is something that you want to describe; the Attributes define the descriptive
            characteristics of the class.</p>
        <p>Attributes may specify the associated National Codes, for example:</p>
        <p><image href="images/attribute.PNG" id="image_bvq_ppm_5mb"/></p>
    </body>
</topic>
